Citation.sAbstract: Isobaric vapour liquid equilibrium (VLE) measurements for the binary systems 4-methyl-2-  pentanone + 1-butanol and 4-methyl-2-pentanone + 2-butanol are reported at 20 and 101.3 kPa. The  system4-methyl-2-pentanone + 1-butanol presents a minimum boiling point azeotrope at both pressures  (20 and 101.3 kPa) and the system 4-methyl-2-pentanone + 2-butanol presents only a minimum boiling  azeotrope at 20 kPa. In both systems, which deviate positively from ideal behaviour, the azeotropic composition  is strongly dependent on pressure. The activity coefficients and boiling points of the solutions  were correlated with itscomposition by the Wilson, UNIQUAC, and NRTL models for which the parameters  are reported.
